        Main constructor of TypeC, sets the correct parameters to be used by the parent class to return a randomly created ArrayList of Strings. Throws an exception in case that the dimensions of the two arraylists don't match or in the case of illegal limit to the desired output.

        Parameters:
        scenario - chosen scenario for the DataExtractor
        d - an ArrayList of type String that contains the list we want to extract content from. It is composed of two
        p - an ArrayList of Integer type that contains the priority values maped one-to-one to the @d parameter.
        o - a two dimensional Java array of type int. First dimension says the priority number, second dimension specifies the absolute value of that priority to extract.

        Verification constructor of TypeC, sets the correct parameters to be used by the parent class to return a randomly created ArrayList of Strings. Throws an exception in case that the dimensions of the two arraylists don't match or in the case of illegal limit to the desired output. Uses a given DataExtractor for the seed.

        Parameters:
        d - an ArrayList of type String that contains the list we want to extract content from. It is composed of two
        p - an ArrayList of Integer type that contains the priority values maped one-to-one to the @d parameter.
        o - a two dimensional Java array of type int. First dimension says the priority number, second dimension specifies the absolute value of that priority to extract.
        de - given DataExtractor to be used for the seed
        Throws:
